1
00:00:17,450 --> 00:00:21,443
<i>[ Umpire ]</i>
<i>Play ball!</i>

2
00:00:27,827 --> 00:00:30,430
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Oh, come on!</i>

3
00:00:30,430 --> 00:00:32,465
Ball four !
Take your base !

4
00:00:32,465 --> 00:00:36,336
<i>[ Chattering ]</i>

5
00:00:36,336 --> 00:00:38,738
That's it, Moose ! You're gettin'
close now. Bring it, son.

6
00:00:38,738 --> 00:00:41,274
Moose couldn't find the plate
if you nailed it to his ass.

7
00:00:41,274 --> 00:00:44,210
Shut your pie hole, Piney.
The kid's gotta learn.

8
00:00:44,210 --> 00:00:47,547
Come straight over the top !
Straight over the top ! Come on !

9
00:00:47,547 --> 00:00:51,540
- <i>[ Chattering Continues ]</i>
- Hot damn. Exley's up.

10
00:00:52,352 --> 00:00:56,345
Back up ! Exley's up !
Back up !

11
00:01:01,227 --> 00:01:04,130
You sure your boy got the right
prescription in those spectacles ?

12
00:01:04,130 --> 00:01:06,566
<i>Oh, don't worry, Ex.</i>
<i>See, I told him to throw it...</i>

13
00:01:06,566 --> 00:01:09,436
right at your big, nappy,
home run-hittin' head.

14
00:01:09,436 --> 00:01:13,429
<i>So you can bet a hundred clams</i>
<i>that ball's goin'anywhere but there.</i>

15
00:01:15,875 --> 00:01:18,678
[ Cheering, Shouting ]

16
00:01:18,678 --> 00:01:22,348
- <i>[ Man ] All the way!</i>
- Foul ! Foul ball ! Foul !

17
00:01:22,348 --> 00:01:26,341
<i>Foul ball!</i>

18
00:01:41,334 --> 00:01:45,327
Let's go. Let's go, now.
Come on. Let's go.

19
00:01:47,841 --> 00:01:51,834
<i>[ Chattering Continues ]</i>

20
00:01:59,452 --> 00:02:02,288
Ball !

21
00:02:02,288 --> 00:02:05,725
- <i>Moose, straight over the top!</i>
- Straight over the top !

22
00:02:05,725 --> 00:02:08,328
- <i>Over the top!</i>
- Hey, Ex,

23
00:02:08,328 --> 00:02:10,597
I heard the Yankees
been callin' you.

24
00:02:10,597 --> 00:02:14,300
I'm fine playin' here
in the Cactus Leagues. Nice and quiet.

25
00:02:14,300 --> 00:02:18,293
<i>[ Indistinct Shouting ]</i>

26
00:02:20,507 --> 00:02:24,477
Ball !
Leave the cactus alone, son !

27
00:02:24,477 --> 00:02:28,314
I don't know, Ex. The Yanks
could use those 60 home runs a year.

28
00:02:28,314 --> 00:02:32,307
Now thatJackie Robinson's
up there in the bigs, people
are sayin' you're gonna be next.

29
00:02:32,852 --> 00:02:36,556
<i>The first black Negro man of color</i>
<i>in the American League.</i>

30
00:02:36,556 --> 00:02:38,625
Shoot, Ex,
you'll be famous, man.

31
00:02:38,625 --> 00:02:42,618
I don't wanna be no famous man.
I just wanna be a man.

32
00:02:43,496 --> 00:02:47,489
- [ All Shouting ]
- Over the top ! Over the top !

33
00:02:52,906 --> 00:02:56,899
<i>[ Umpire ]</i>
<i>It's a good one!</i>

34
00:02:57,810 --> 00:03:01,247
- That's the key, baby !
- Fair ball ! Home run ! Home run !

35
00:03:01,247 --> 00:03:05,251
- <i>[ Cheering Continues ]</i>
- Sixty-one.

36
00:03:05,251 --> 00:03:09,244
[ Laughing, Shouting ]

37
00:03:24,904 --> 00:03:28,897
Hey, what's that ?

38
00:03:35,882 --> 00:03:39,252
[ Horses Neighing ]

39
00:03:39,252 --> 00:03:42,855
What do you boys want ?
We're just playin' a baseball game here.

40
00:03:42,855 --> 00:03:46,426
We got no beef with you, sir. It's
that black Babe Ruth hidin' behind you.

41
00:03:46,426 --> 00:03:48,962
<i>Josh Exley.</i>
<i>That's all we come for.</i>

42
00:03:48,962 --> 00:03:50,964
Well, you can't have him.

43
00:03:50,964 --> 00:03:54,467
We heard the Yankees want to let
a little nigger play ball !

44
00:03:54,467 --> 00:03:58,438
<i>So we just figured we gotta play</i>
<i>with him a little bit some first.</i>

45
00:03:58,438 --> 00:04:02,408
<i>And all you niggers</i>
<i>and nigger lovers...</i>

46
00:04:02,408 --> 00:04:04,410
can go home !

47
00:04:04,410 --> 00:04:06,846
It's Ex we want.

48
00:04:06,846 --> 00:04:09,482
[ Grunts ]

49
00:04:09,482 --> 00:04:13,475
<i>That's what I'm talkin'about.</i>
<i>Straight over the top.</i>
<i>Come in straight over the top with it.</i>

50
00:04:16,556 --> 00:04:20,549
<i>Straight over the top.</i>
<i>Come on, kid.</i>

51
00:04:21,027 --> 00:04:24,597
Come on, get the guns.
Get the guns !

52
00:04:24,597 --> 00:04:28,590
<i>Boys ain't so tough without</i>
<i>your shotguns, are ya, fellas ?</i>

53
00:04:28,901 --> 00:04:32,894
You ain't nothin' but a coward,
hidin' behind your mama's bedsheet.

54
00:04:33,806 --> 00:04:37,799
Let's see your face.

55
00:04:38,911 --> 00:04:42,904
Holy Mother--

56
00:05:18,751 --> 00:05:22,121
[ T<i>V</i> Sportscaster]
It's a gorgeous day for baseball
here in the City of the Angels,

57
00:05:22,121 --> 00:05:26,114
and I'm told it's a gorgeous day
all over our republic today...

58
00:05:26,326 --> 00:05:30,319
from Bangor to Bellflower,
from Amarillo to Anchorage.

59
00:05:30,663 --> 00:05:34,656
- <i>The sun is shining, and it's</i>
<i>a perfect day to play baseball.</i>
- <i>Morning.</i>

60
00:05:35,001 --> 00:05:38,994
<i>Eddie Brez will start it off</i>--
<i>[ Continues, Indistinct ]</i>

61
00:05:51,351 --> 00:05:54,887
Mulder, it is such
a gorgeous day outside.

62
00:05:54,887 --> 00:05:57,357
Have you ever
entertained the idea...

63
00:05:57,357 --> 00:05:59,459
of trying to find life
on <i>this</i> planet ?

64
00:05:59,459 --> 00:06:02,128
I've seen the life
on this planet, Scully,

65
00:06:02,128 --> 00:06:06,121
and that is exactly
why I'm looking elsewhere.

66
00:06:10,737 --> 00:06:14,140
Did you bring enough ice cream
to share with the rest of the class ?

67
00:06:14,140 --> 00:06:16,142
It's not ice cream.

68
00:06:16,142 --> 00:06:19,011
It's a nonfat Tofutti rice dreamsicle.

69
00:06:19,011 --> 00:06:22,915
Ugh ! I bet the air in my mouth
tastes better than that.

70
00:06:22,915 --> 00:06:25,017
You sure know
how to live it up, Scully.

71
00:06:25,017 --> 00:06:28,654
Oh, you're Mr. Live It Up.
You're really...

72
00:06:28,654 --> 00:06:31,891
Mr. Squeeze Every Last Drop
Out OfThis Sweet Life.

73
00:06:31,891 --> 00:06:35,884
On this precious Saturday, you've
got us grabbing life by the testes.

74
00:06:37,063 --> 00:06:39,699
Stealing reference books
from the F.B.I. library...

75
00:06:39,699 --> 00:06:42,769
in order to go through
New Mexico obituaries...

76
00:06:42,769 --> 00:06:45,671
for the years 1 940 to 1 949.

77
00:06:45,671 --> 00:06:47,673
And for what joyful purpose ?

78
00:06:47,673 --> 00:06:49,675
Looking for anomalies, Scully.

79
00:06:49,675 --> 00:06:53,546
Do you know how many so-called flying
disc reports there were in the 1 940s ?

80
00:06:53,546 --> 00:06:56,182
<i>I don't care. Mulder, this</i>
<i>is a needle in a haystack.</i>

81
00:06:56,182 --> 00:06:59,152
These poor souls have
been dead for 50 years.

82
00:06:59,152 --> 00:07:01,687
Let them rest in peace.
Let sleeping dogs lie.

83
00:07:01,687 --> 00:07:04,524
Well, I won't sit idly by
as you hurl cliches at me.

84
00:07:04,524 --> 00:07:06,192
Preparation is the father
of inspiration.

85
00:07:06,192 --> 00:07:07,927
Necessity is the mother
of invention.

86
00:07:07,927 --> 00:07:09,996
The road of excess
leads to the palace of wisdom.

87
00:07:09,996 --> 00:07:11,998
Eat, drink and be merry,
for tomorrow we may die.

88
00:07:11,998 --> 00:07:15,835
I scream, you scream, we all scream
for nonfat Tofutti rice dreamsicles.

89
00:07:15,835 --> 00:07:19,672
Nooooo !

90
00:07:19,672 --> 00:07:22,708
Mulder.

91
00:07:22,708 --> 00:07:26,701
<i>Mulder! You cheat!</i>

92
00:07:26,913 --> 00:07:30,249
I can't believe it ! You've been
reading about baseball this whole time.

93
00:07:30,249 --> 00:07:32,852
I'm reading the box scores,
Scully. You'd like it.

94
00:07:32,852 --> 00:07:34,854
It's like the
Pythagorean Theorem for jocks.

95
00:07:34,854 --> 00:07:36,889
<i>It distills all the chaos</i>
<i>and action...</i>

96
00:07:36,889 --> 00:07:39,125
of any game in the history
of all baseball games...

97
00:07:39,125 --> 00:07:41,928
into one tiny, perfect
rectangular sequence of numbers.

98
00:07:41,928 --> 00:07:45,731
I can look at this box, and I can
recreate exactly what happened...

99
00:07:45,731 --> 00:07:48,835
on some sunny summer day
back in 1 947.

100
00:07:48,835 --> 00:07:51,471
<i>It's like the numbers talk to me.</i>
<i>They comfort me.</i>

101
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:55,464
They tell me that even though
lots of things can change, some
things remain the same. It's--

102
00:07:55,775 --> 00:07:58,478
Boring.

103
00:07:58,478 --> 00:08:01,180
Mulder, can I ask you
a personal question ?

104
00:08:01,180 --> 00:08:03,015
Of course not.

105
00:08:03,015 --> 00:08:07,008
<i>Did your mother ever tell you</i>
<i>to go outside and play?</i>

106
00:08:07,787 --> 00:08:10,156
Is that Arthur Dales ?

107
00:08:10,156 --> 00:08:12,825
<i>Mulder?</i>

108
00:08:12,825 --> 00:08:16,229
[ Fake Sneeze ]

109
00:08:16,229 --> 00:08:19,899
You just defaced property
of the U.S. government.

110
00:08:19,899 --> 00:08:21,901
<i>[ Sportscaster On Radio ]</i>
<i>It is gone!</i>

111
00:08:21,901 --> 00:08:25,894
You rebel.

112
00:08:35,748 --> 00:08:38,317
What in the hell
took you so long ?

113
00:08:38,317 --> 00:08:40,553
I'm sorry, sir.
I'm looking for Arthur Dales.

114
00:08:40,553 --> 00:08:44,090
- I'm Arthur Dales.
- No, you're not.

115
00:08:44,090 --> 00:08:46,192
Don't be a wiseass, son.

116
00:08:46,192 --> 00:08:50,162
No, I'm-I'm sorry, sir. I know Arthur
Dales, and you're not Arthur Dales.

117
00:08:50,162 --> 00:08:54,133
Arthur Dales is my brother.
My name also happens to be Arthur Dales.

118
00:08:54,133 --> 00:08:56,135
It's the same name,
different guy.

119
00:08:56,135 --> 00:08:59,105
The other Arthur, he moved
to Florida, the lucky bastard.

120
00:08:59,105 --> 00:09:03,098
Our parents weren't exactly big
in the imagination department
when it came to names.

121
00:09:04,043 --> 00:09:08,036
If it'll help you wrapping your little
head around this stupefying mystery,

122
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:12,552
Agent Mulder, we had a sister
named Arthur too.

123
00:09:12,552 --> 00:09:14,554
And a goldfish.

124
00:09:14,554 --> 00:09:16,656
How do you know my name ?

125
00:09:16,656 --> 00:09:18,891
My brother told me all about you.

126
00:09:18,891 --> 00:09:22,884
He said you were the biggest jackass
in the bureau since he retired.

127
00:09:23,629 --> 00:09:25,698
Yeah, we're big fans.

128
00:09:25,698 --> 00:09:29,691
Sometimes we'd stay awake for hours
at night just talking about you.

129
00:09:30,336 --> 00:09:32,338
Just fascinating.

130
00:09:32,338 --> 00:09:36,331
Now, unless you're hiding some
Chinese food, let's call it a day.

131
00:09:42,181 --> 00:09:46,174
Mr. Dales, I have a, uh--
I have a photo here of your brother.

132
00:09:46,686 --> 00:09:49,255
Maybe it's you.
It's from many years ago,

133
00:09:49,255 --> 00:09:51,824
and you're standing
in Roswell, New Mexico.

134
00:09:51,824 --> 00:09:55,817
<i>Roswell. That's me.</i>
<i>I was a cop once in Roswell.</i>

135
00:09:55,962 --> 00:09:58,998
Okay. And you're standing with
Negro League legend Josh Exley,

136
00:09:58,998 --> 00:10:02,969
who disappeared without a trace during
a season in which he hit 60 home runs.

137
00:10:02,969 --> 00:10:06,272
-<i>Sixty</i>-<i>one!</i>
- Sixty-one home runs in 1 948.

138
00:10:06,272 --> 00:10:08,975
- <i>Forty</i>-<i>seven.</i>
- Forty-seven, whatever.

139
00:10:08,975 --> 00:10:11,143
I don't really care
about the baseball so much.

140
00:10:11,143 --> 00:10:13,312
What I care about is this man
in the picture with you...

141
00:10:13,312 --> 00:10:15,715
I believe to be an
alien bounty hunter.

142
00:10:15,715 --> 00:10:19,218
Of course you don't care
about the baseball, Mr. Mulder.

143
00:10:19,218 --> 00:10:21,821
You only bothered my brother
about the important things...

144
00:10:21,821 --> 00:10:24,724
like government conspiracies
and alien bounty hunters...

145
00:10:24,724 --> 00:10:26,826
and the truth
with a capital ""T.""

146
00:10:26,826 --> 00:10:29,428
- Wait a minute. I like baseball.
- You like baseball, huh ?

147
00:10:29,428 --> 00:10:33,421
- Yeah.
- How many home runs
did Mickey Mantle hit ?

148
00:10:35,368 --> 00:10:38,037
- A hundred and sixty-three.
- [ Scoffs ]

149
00:10:38,037 --> 00:10:42,030
Righty, 373 lefty, 536 total.

150
00:10:45,111 --> 00:10:49,104
<i>[ Dales ] What you fail to understand</i>
<i>in yourjoyless myopia...</i>

151
00:10:49,281 --> 00:10:52,685
<i>is that baseball</i>
<i>is the key to life.</i>

152
00:10:52,685 --> 00:10:55,154
The Rosetta Stone,
if you will.

153
00:10:55,154 --> 00:10:59,147
If you just understood baseball better,
all your other questions, your--

154
00:10:59,892 --> 00:11:03,062
the aliens, the conspiracies--

155
00:11:03,062 --> 00:11:06,265
they would all in their way
be answered by the baseball gods.

156
00:11:06,265 --> 00:11:08,434
Yes, sir.
That may be true.

157
00:11:08,434 --> 00:11:10,736
I'm thinking that your
experience in Roswell...

158
00:11:10,736 --> 00:11:14,674
could be germane to a conspiracy
between our government and these
shape-shifting alien beings.

159
00:11:14,674 --> 00:11:16,942
Oh, don't bore me, son.

160
00:11:16,942 --> 00:11:20,012
My brother Arthur
started the X-Files,

161
00:11:20,012 --> 00:11:23,883
the Federal Bureau of Obfuscation,
before you were born.

162
00:11:23,883 --> 00:11:26,485
He was working for the F.B.I.,
hunting for aliens...

163
00:11:26,485 --> 00:11:29,288
when you were watching
<i>My Best Friend's Martians.</i>

164
00:11:29,288 --> 00:11:32,324
<i>You say</i> ""<i>shape</i>-<i>shifting.</i> ""

165
00:11:32,324 --> 00:11:35,695
<i>Agent Mulder, do you believe...</i>

166
00:11:35,695 --> 00:11:39,688
that love can
make a man shape-shift ?

167
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:42,835
[ Chuckles ]

168
00:11:42,835 --> 00:11:45,905
I guess women change men
all the time.

169
00:11:45,905 --> 00:11:49,341
I'm not talking about women.
I'm talking about love, passion.

170
00:11:49,341 --> 00:11:52,812
Like the passion you have
for proving extraterrestrial life.

171
00:11:52,812 --> 00:11:56,805
<i>Do you believe that that passion</i>
<i>can change your very nature ?</i>

172
00:11:57,850 --> 00:12:01,843
Can make you shape-shift from a man
into something other than a man ?

173
00:12:04,857 --> 00:12:08,850
What exactly has your
brother told you about me ?

174
00:12:11,030 --> 00:12:14,734
Mr. Dales, if you and your brother have
really known about this bounty hunter...

175
00:12:14,734 --> 00:12:18,437
and plans for colonization
for 50 years, why the hell
wouldn't you have told anybody ?

176
00:12:18,437 --> 00:12:20,973
- Nobody would believe me.
- I would have believed you.

177
00:12:20,973 --> 00:12:24,944
- No. You weren't ripe.
- Not ripe ?

178
00:12:24,944 --> 00:12:27,446
Let me tell you something.
I've been ripe for years.

179
00:12:27,446 --> 00:12:30,049
I am way past ripe.
I'm so ripe, I'm rotten.

180
00:12:30,049 --> 00:12:34,019
This cuts to the very heart
of the mystery of what I've been
doing for the past ten years.

181
00:12:34,019 --> 00:12:38,012
Oh, the heart of the mystery !
The heart of the mystery !

182
00:12:38,124 --> 00:12:42,117
Ah, there you are !

183
00:12:42,461 --> 00:12:46,265
Mr. Mulder, maybe
you'd better start paying...

184
00:12:46,265 --> 00:12:49,168
a little less attention
to the heart of the mystery...

185
00:12:49,168 --> 00:12:52,238
and a little more attention
to the mystery of the heart.

186
00:12:52,238 --> 00:12:55,274
- You got a dime ?
- What is this ?

187
00:12:55,274 --> 00:12:58,444
This little fella goes
by the name of Pete Rosebud.

188
00:12:58,444 --> 00:13:01,881
If you keep pumping coffee money
into him, he'll tell you a story...

189
00:13:01,881 --> 00:13:05,184
about baseball
and aliens and bounty hunters.

190
00:13:05,184 --> 00:13:07,353
You're making me
feel like a child.

191
00:13:07,353 --> 00:13:10,890
Perfect. That's exactly the right place
to start from, isn't it ?

192
00:13:10,890 --> 00:13:13,826
Now, the first thing you
gotta know about baseball is...

193
00:13:13,826 --> 00:13:17,819
it keeps you forever young.

194
00:13:31,477 --> 00:13:34,446
[ Laughter]

195
00:13:34,446 --> 00:13:37,883
Mr. Exley ? Mr. Exley,
my name's Arthur Dales.

196
00:13:37,883 --> 00:13:41,876
I'm an employee of
the Roswell Police Department.

197
00:13:42,621 --> 00:13:46,025
- Have I broken a law, sir ?
- You stole !

198
00:13:46,025 --> 00:13:48,828
Second base in the third inning.
I'm a witness.

199
00:13:48,828 --> 00:13:52,097
Officer, I seen that steal.
At least 50 bases this year.

200
00:13:52,097 --> 00:13:55,234
No, sir, you haven't broken any laws.
Not that I'm aware of.

201
00:13:55,234 --> 00:13:59,205
I've been assigned by my superiors
to protect you against certain parties.

202
00:13:59,205 --> 00:14:02,041
I'm the one that need protection
from certain parties.

203
00:14:02,041 --> 00:14:04,443
Exley, he in bed
by 8:00 every night.

204
00:14:04,443 --> 00:14:07,613
Yeah. I appreciate your concern,
sir, but I can protect myself.

205
00:14:07,613 --> 00:14:10,950
Mr. Exley, I'm not a big sports
hero like yourself, sir,

206
00:14:10,950 --> 00:14:14,943
and I really don't have an opinion
on Negroes... orJews or Communists...

207
00:14:15,087 --> 00:14:17,423
or even Canadians and
vegetarians, for that matter.

208
00:14:17,423 --> 00:14:20,860
But I cannot stomach the murder of a man
of any persuasion or any color...

209
00:14:20,860 --> 00:14:23,629
being flaunted and solicited
in my town, not on my watch.

210
00:14:23,629 --> 00:14:26,398
<i>So you can be safe with me</i>
<i>in a cell down at the precinct,</i>

211
00:14:26,398 --> 00:14:29,068
or you can be safe with me
here on the bus.

212
00:14:29,068 --> 00:14:33,061
Seeing as how this is still America,
you're free to choose, sir.

213
00:14:39,612 --> 00:14:43,605
- [ Chattering ]
- [ Indistinct Muttering ]

214
00:14:50,222 --> 00:14:53,325
Hey, Officer Dales,
